<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 1:35PM MDT  by NWS Billings</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Carter
County through 215 PM MDT...
At 134 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles north of Alzada, or 45 miles northwest of Belle Fourche, moving
southeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Albion.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
